Wait a minute!

04:15.030 --> 04:16.365
What is this?

04:16.430 --> 04:17.800
Well, who are you?

04:17.867 --> 04:19.902
I'm Barney Hopkins,
producer of this show.

04:19.969 --> 04:21.837
Oh, yeah? Well,
that's tough luck, brother.

04:21.904 --> 04:23.739
I'm from the sheriff's office.

04:23.806 --> 04:26.576
Legal attachment
to collect for the credit.

04:26.642 --> 04:29.144
Corpus delecti
or seize the body.

04:29.211 --> 04:30.245
What? Again?

04:31.413 --> 04:33.248
Don't you dare!

04:33.315 --> 04:36.151
Don't worry sis. This'll look
nice in the sheriff's office.

04:36.218 --> 04:37.953
(male #2)
Break down
that scenery!

04:38.020 --> 04:39.288
What's the excitement?

04:39.354 --> 04:41.156
It means they closed
the show, dumbbell.

04:41.223 --> 04:43.158
(male #3)
Here, give me that costume!

04:43.225 --> 04:45.995
- I beg your pardon!
- We got to take it back.

04:46.061 --> 04:48.363
Well, that's as far
back as it goes.

04:48.430 --> 04:51.634
- We gotta have that costume.
- At least leave me carfare.

04:51.701 --> 04:53.102
What for?

04:53.168 --> 04:55.638
This is our dress rehearsal.
We got a great show.

04:55.705 --> 05:00.409
It opens tomorrow. Don't do this
because I don't pay few bills.

05:00.475 --> 05:02.444
When the show opens
I will pay them.

05:02.511 --> 05:05.280
Tell it to the sheriff.

05:05.347 --> 05:09.451
This is the fourth in two months
that I've been in and out of.

05:09.518 --> 05:11.887
They close before they open.

05:11.954 --> 05:14.590
The depression, deary.

05:51.026 --> 05:54.830
I can remember when that
alarm clock used to ring.

05:54.897 --> 05:57.266
Those good old days
when you had to get up.

05:57.332 --> 06:00.202
Come on. Let's get up
and look for work.

06:00.269 --> 06:02.004
I hate starving in bed.

06:02.071 --> 06:05.074
Name me a better
place to starve.

06:05.140 --> 06:06.809
Your stomach.

06:06.876 --> 06:10.079
Well, let's get up
and get dressed.

06:10.145 --> 06:12.782
I thought we might
try the flea circus.

06:12.848 --> 06:14.850
Maybe they got something
for us there.

06:14.917 --> 06:17.552
What can we get
at a flea circus?

06:17.619 --> 06:19.188
Fleas.

06:19.254 --> 06:20.723
You can get those here.

06:20.790 --> 06:23.926
Alright, come on.
Let's get up.

06:23.993 --> 06:25.327
One.

06:25.394 --> 06:27.162
'Two.'

06:27.229 --> 06:28.964
Three.

06:34.704 --> 06:38.040
- How about some nourishment?
- What's on the menu, Trixie?

06:38.107 --> 06:40.109
We'll see what
the neighbors have to offer.

06:40.175 --> 06:42.111
Cut the bread and set the table.

06:42.177 --> 06:45.214
- Have we any bread?
- Yeah. Have we any table?

07:03.699 --> 07:05.334
Ha ha ha!

07:05.400 --> 07:08.237
What neighbors,
oh, what neighbors.

07:08.303 --> 07:11.540
I can remember not so long ago,
a penthouse on Park Avenue

07:11.606 --> 07:15.044
with a real tree and flowers
a fountain, and a French maid.

07:15.110 --> 07:17.913
And a warm bath
with salt from Yardley's.

07:17.980 --> 07:20.049
And a little dress
that Schiaparelli ran up.

07:20.115 --> 07:23.318
And a snappy roadster
and a ride through the park.

07:23.385 --> 07:24.987
And now stealing milk.

07:25.054 --> 07:27.422
That's alright. The dairy
company stole it from a cow.

07:27.489 --> 07:31.093
About a year ago at this time,
I was on my way to Havana.

07:31.160 --> 07:33.328
The birds were singing,
and the sky was blue.

07:33.395 --> 07:35.564
I said to the mug
in the next pew

07:35.630 --> 07:38.000
"I need a couple
of hundred dollars, big boy."

07:38.067 --> 07:42.271
and he said,
"In my pants pocket."

07:42.337 --> 07:44.273
I reached over and took $500

07:44.339 --> 07:47.009
out of his back pants pocket
just like that.

07:47.076 --> 07:50.780
All I got left are his pajamas
and I'm a milk snatcher.

07:50.846 --> 07:52.214
[knock on door]

07:52.281 --> 07:54.416
Guess we got to give it back.

07:55.550 --> 07:56.718
[knock on door]

07:56.786 --> 07:59.088
Maybe it's the piano remover.

08:04.426 --> 08:05.460
Fay!

08:05.527 --> 08:07.329
Who'd you think
it was? The wolf?

08:07.396 --> 08:11.233
If it was, we'd eat it. Why
the blue spectacles, grandma?

08:11.300 --> 08:13.602
So the landlady
won't recognize me.

08:13.668 --> 08:16.238
I'm obligated to her
for a little item called rent.

08:16.305 --> 08:19.508
Well, if you've come to make
a touch, the bank has folded.

08:19.574 --> 08:21.877
Your millions are safe, Trixie.

08:21.944 --> 08:24.213
I came to tell
you gals good news.

08:24.279 --> 08:26.748
Barney's putting on a new show.

08:26.816 --> 08:28.283
- Barney?
- Barney Hopkins?

08:28.350 --> 08:30.285
Rehearsals start in two weeks.

08:30.352 --> 08:33.355
- He must have found an angel.
- Let's go over and find out.

08:33.422 --> 08:35.590
When the mob finds out,
they'll be after him.

08:35.657 --> 08:39.428
We can't all go. We haven't got
decent clothing left for one.

08:39.494 --> 08:43.265
Yeah, if one doesn't look modish
with Barney, it's thumbs down.

08:43.332 --> 08:47.102
Let's scare up to make one of us
look, as you say, modish.

08:47.169 --> 08:48.971
- Who's to go?
- Let's match for it.

08:49.038 --> 08:50.172
- Taxis!
- Yellow!

08:50.239 --> 08:51.673
- Checker!
- Red-top!

08:51.740 --> 08:53.208
Black and white!

09:04.219 --> 09:06.688
- Checkers.
- Aw, Carol wins.

09:06.755 --> 09:09.758
Aw, gee. I look much better in
clothes than any of you.

09:09.825 --> 09:13.963
- If Barney sees me in clothes--
- He wouldn't recognize you.

09:14.029 --> 09:15.664
What happened
to your lovely-mink coat?

09:15.730 --> 09:18.600
Uncle's got it, got everything.
We even hocked our inlays.

09:18.667 --> 09:21.103
- Honey, give me my stockings.
- Sure, there they are.

09:21.170 --> 09:23.873
Fay, you got to give
Carol that dress.

09:23.939 --> 09:27.642
- I've to go to the drugstore.
- We'll give you something good.

09:27.709 --> 09:29.444
The dress belongs to them.

09:29.511 --> 09:31.413
- I'm a hostess there.
- Stand still.

09:31.480 --> 09:32.948
So am I a hostess.

09:33.015 --> 09:36.218
Got to entertain Barney
with the idea of giving us work.

09:38.087 --> 09:40.856
Don't forget to stand in light
when you're talking to Barney.

09:40.923 --> 09:44.459
They know what they're doing
when they dress their hostesses.

09:44.526 --> 09:46.128
You don't look bad.

09:46.195 --> 09:48.163
Take these papers, get through
the enemy's lines.

09:48.230 --> 09:51.100
- Ride like blazes. Taxi fare.
- Lots of luck, Carol.

09:51.166 --> 09:54.636
Thanks. Well, here we go.
Laughing and wondering.

09:54.703 --> 09:58.240
Watch yourself in the clinches.
Dress belongs to the drugstore.

09:58.307 --> 10:00.375
I'd like to meet that druggist.

10:00.442 --> 10:04.846
The best comedienne on Broadway
will proceed to make beds.

10:04.914 --> 10:07.349
Well, I'm going to get
a glass of milk.

10:07.416 --> 10:09.518
[piano music]

10:22.797 --> 10:28.603
* In the shadows
let me come and sing to you *

10:30.239 --> 10:36.478
* Let me dream a song
that I can bring to you *

10:38.413 --> 10:44.219
* Take me in your arms
and let me cling to you *

10:45.720 --> 10:51.526
* Let me linger long

10:51.593 --> 10:57.366
* Let me lilt my song

10:57.432 --> 11:03.973
* In the winter let me
bring the spring to you *

11:05.740 --> 11:12.514
* Let me feel that I mean
everything to you *

11:14.649 --> 11:19.288
* Love's old song *

11:20.855 --> 11:24.326
* Will be new

