(Trixie)
'I knew he was somebody.
You can't fool me.'

43:10.864 --> 43:14.067
Trixie Lorraine, you thought
I was a fool to be involved.

43:14.134 --> 43:16.269
You don't know when I'm kidding.

43:19.873 --> 43:21.208
Mr. Bradford?

43:21.274 --> 43:23.410
- He's on the lounge, sir.
- Thank you.

43:25.778 --> 43:27.948
- Good morning.
- Good morning. You're late.

43:28.015 --> 43:30.117
- Not much, am I?
- 17 minutes.

43:30.183 --> 43:32.119
- Hello, Peabody.
- How are you, young man?

43:32.185 --> 43:33.653
- Sit down.
- Thank you.

43:33.720 --> 43:35.655
I'll come directly
to the point, Robert.

43:35.722 --> 43:38.258
Your family's greatly disturbed
over what has occurred.

43:38.325 --> 43:40.894
I hope you appreciate that
I flew here this morning

43:40.961 --> 43:42.362
in uncertain weather.

43:42.429 --> 43:44.797
As trustee of your estate
and your elder brother

43:44.864 --> 43:46.566
I represent the family

43:46.633 --> 43:48.635
in saying that
we cannot have you mixed-up

43:48.701 --> 43:51.171
in this theater business.
You know how he feel.

43:51.238 --> 43:54.007
Your mother is greatly concerned
and every member of your family.

43:54.074 --> 43:56.643
I cannot begin to describe
to you, my dear boy

43:56.709 --> 43:58.345
the extent of the shock.

43:58.411 --> 44:00.347
I'm sorry everybody
in the family's shocked

44:00.413 --> 44:02.582
but I'd better come
directly to the point too.

44:02.649 --> 44:05.585
- Music is my career.
- Music, yes, but--

44:05.652 --> 44:08.655
The kind that's sung in shows.
Over the radio and on records.

44:08.721 --> 44:11.491
I don't mean the music played by
the Boston symphony orchestra.

44:11.558 --> 44:13.526
You have to be half-dead
to compose that.

44:13.593 --> 44:16.363
I wanna write this other kind.
This show was my opportunity.

44:16.429 --> 44:19.532
The show clicked
and I'm going on with it.

44:19.599 --> 44:22.369
As to appearing with the show
I know how you feel.

44:22.435 --> 44:25.838
I did my best to stay out of it
but an emergency came up

44:25.905 --> 44:29.642
I had to do it. I can't let them
down. Besides, I like it.

44:29.709 --> 44:32.679
Though the family regrets
that one who bears our name

44:32.745 --> 44:35.748
should go in for this sort of...
sensational career.

44:35.815 --> 44:37.684
In preference to banking

44:37.750 --> 44:39.652
nevertheless, we've agreed
not to oppose you.

44:39.719 --> 44:42.822
One thing, however, we must
and will insist upon.

44:42.889 --> 44:44.657
And what's that?

44:44.724 --> 44:46.126
This girl.

44:46.193 --> 44:48.561
This show girl whose name
is linked with yours.

44:48.628 --> 44:50.263
Polly Parker.

44:50.330 --> 44:52.599
- Well, what of it?
- What of it? Simply this--

44:52.665 --> 44:54.834
Listen, before you say anything,
you better know this.

44:54.901 --> 44:58.305
I'm in love with Polly Parker
and I'm going to marry her!

44:58.371 --> 44:59.539
What?

44:59.606 --> 45:01.774
I'm going to complain
to the house committee.

45:01.841 --> 45:03.576
Just what I said.

45:03.643 --> 45:05.578
You marry this
cheap-little-show girl?

45:05.645 --> 45:09.116
Wait a minute. That's pretty
much of an old-fashioned idea.

45:09.182 --> 45:11.985
Families don't interfere
with love affairs nowadays.

45:12.052 --> 45:13.786
If they do, it doesn't
mean anything.

45:13.853 --> 45:17.157
If you marry that girl you'll
get not one cent of income.

45:17.224 --> 45:19.592
I don't have to remind you
until you are 30

45:19.659 --> 45:21.828
I have the right
to cut off your income.

45:21.894 --> 45:25.865
If that's all you have to say
to me, you're wasting your time.

45:25.932 --> 45:28.635
I've got more important
things to do!

45:28.701 --> 45:31.871
I shall certainly complain
to the house committee.

45:31.938 --> 45:33.673
I can't understand it.

45:33.740 --> 45:36.376
It's the girl. I know
these show girls.

45:36.443 --> 45:38.911
They're little parasites,
gold diggers.

45:38.978 --> 45:40.247
I don't doubt it.

45:40.313 --> 45:42.282
I remember in my early youth

45:42.349 --> 45:44.951
I trod the primrose path
on the great white way.

45:45.018 --> 45:46.953
There I learned the bitter truth

45:47.020 --> 45:48.955
that all women of the theater

45:49.022 --> 45:50.957
were chiselers, parasites

45:51.024 --> 45:52.959
or as we call them gold diggers.

45:53.026 --> 45:56.129
I remember well
one experience I had

45:56.196 --> 45:58.831
with a woman of the theater.

45:58.898 --> 46:01.434
It was the day
of the big Harvard game.

46:01.501 --> 46:04.937
We all came down,
a stout company of young blades

46:05.004 --> 46:07.774
eager to learn about life.

46:07.840 --> 46:11.811
I met this girl at the
stage door of the old casino.

46:11.878 --> 46:14.147
'We went to rector's
for a bite.'

46:14.214 --> 46:16.183
I had a cold bird and a bottle.

46:16.249 --> 46:18.185
She nibbled at a steak.

46:18.251 --> 46:23.156
Her name was Eunice.
She called me "fuffy."

46:24.624 --> 46:28.161
I don't know why she did,
but she called me "fuffy."

46:28.228 --> 46:29.662
I'm going to see her.

46:29.729 --> 46:32.299
I don't know where she is.
It's been 30 years.

46:32.365 --> 46:34.134
No, no. I mean
this Polly Parker woman.

46:34.201 --> 46:37.704
I wouldn't if I were you. You're
putting yourself in their hands.

46:37.770 --> 46:40.640
They're all blackmailers,
gold diggers, parasites.

46:42.209 --> 46:44.177
I resign!

46:44.244 --> 46:46.146
- No.
- Yes.

