'I will, Trixie.'

47:12.139 --> 47:14.241
[doorbell buzzing]

47:14.307 --> 47:16.243
(Carol)
'Come in! Come in!'

47:16.309 --> 47:20.380
* One by one
they vanish in the sky *

47:20.447 --> 47:24.651
* I try to smile
and face the sun *

47:24.717 --> 47:29.522
* But romance passes by *

47:32.091 --> 47:33.726
Well, who is it?

47:33.793 --> 47:36.463
I am J. Lawrence Bradford.

47:38.365 --> 47:40.333
Yes?

47:40.400 --> 47:42.635
I've come to see
Ms. Polly Parker.

47:42.702 --> 47:44.204
Oh, yes.

47:44.271 --> 47:46.339
I'm the brother
of Robert Treat Bradford

47:46.406 --> 47:48.575
'whom you probably know
as Brad Roberts.'

47:48.641 --> 47:50.577
Oh, you are Brad's brother.

47:50.643 --> 47:52.779
Sit down. I'll be
dressed in a minute.

47:52.845 --> 47:54.781
(Lawrence)
'Don't bother, Ms. Parker.'

47:54.847 --> 47:58.651
- But you see, I'm not--
- Please, Ms. Parker.

47:58.718 --> 48:00.653
'I have just spoken
to my brother.'

48:00.720 --> 48:02.755
'He tells me he wants
to marry you.'

48:02.822 --> 48:05.091
You're making a mistake.
Let me explain--

48:05.158 --> 48:06.893
Don't bother to explain.

48:06.959 --> 48:10.497
If he disgraces the family
by marrying a show girl

48:10.563 --> 48:12.499
the family is through with him.

48:12.565 --> 48:15.668
Did you say disgrace the family
by marrying a show girl?

48:15.735 --> 48:17.237
I said exactly that.

48:17.304 --> 48:19.772
Show girls are reputed to be

48:19.839 --> 48:22.275
parasites, chiselers,
gold diggers.

48:22.342 --> 48:25.645
Oh! Show girls
are excellent in their way

48:25.712 --> 48:28.781
attractive creatures,
even fascinating

48:28.848 --> 48:31.651
but hardly fitted to shine
in the upper social circles.

48:31.718 --> 48:34.487
(Lawrence)
'This is not directed against
you personally, Ms. Parker.'

48:34.554 --> 48:36.623
No, I understand that.
Not personally.

48:36.689 --> 48:39.992
All show girls are parasites,
chiselers and gold diggers.

48:40.059 --> 48:41.394
