'Exactly.'

48:41.461 --> 48:43.396
You'd better let me
tell you that--

48:43.463 --> 48:46.933
- Just tell me how much.
- How much what?

48:46.999 --> 48:48.435
What is your price?

48:48.501 --> 48:51.704
How much do you want to release
Robert from marrying you?

48:51.771 --> 48:53.740
Well, this is very funny.

48:53.806 --> 48:56.643
I see nothing amusing
in it, Ms. parker.

48:56.709 --> 48:58.878
Please, don't let's
waste time. How much?

48:58.945 --> 49:00.980
- I'm sorry.
- 'Sorry?'

49:01.047 --> 49:02.515
No price on me.

49:02.582 --> 49:04.784
I insist, Ms. Parker.
You must have a price.

49:04.851 --> 49:08.455
I am inclined to be generous
in the matter.

49:08.521 --> 49:11.324
After all, I realize that
Bob is a headstrong boy.

49:11.391 --> 49:15.995
I'm in charge of him and I feel
I know what is best for him.

49:16.062 --> 49:18.197
I've had about enough of this.

49:21.100 --> 49:22.602
If you don't mind.

49:22.669 --> 49:27.840
Oh, I beg your pardon,
but am I interrupting?

49:27.907 --> 49:29.376
No, not at all.

49:29.442 --> 49:32.812
This is Brad's brother,
J. Lawrence Bradford.

49:32.879 --> 49:34.581
I'm charmed.

49:34.647 --> 49:36.849
Beware. Trixie's a show girl.

49:36.916 --> 49:39.452
And who is this
distinguished-looking young man?

49:39.519 --> 49:40.520
